  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to be able to save an address in the Transaction Status page **so that** I can quickly choose it for future transactions\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nThis issue is to connect the RPC endpoint for a wallet address to be saved and the data persisted.\r\n\r\nFigma design: https://www.figma.com/file/HKncH4wnDwZDAhc4AryK8Y/Wallet-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=1518-358506&mode=design&t=bR18stv43uRLwfK3-4\r\n\r\n\r\nVisual reference:\r\n <img width=\"180\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/18485527/8ec03a21-10f4-49ef-8485-935c553b43a3\"> <img width=\"180\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/18485527/8dc6a79a-8944-4d62-8ed9-6e2360a9b0e5\"> <img width=\"180\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/18485527/bc332a83-87ff-4115-bb57-7405b3e65bda\"> \r\n<img width=\"180\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/18485527/6c98b437-54a2-42bf-96d0-b38d7482b98d\">\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- [ ] When user types a name for the address, initials in the top rounded box should be updated and \"Save address\" button should be enabled.\r\n- [ ] When input looses focus, edit button should appear at the right of the input. User can press edit button to edit name again.\r\n- [ ] When input is focused, char count view should appear. \r\n- [ ] Max characters count for the name is 24.\r\n- [ ] User can set a Color for that address. Background gradient should update to reflect selected Color, whenever selected Color changes.\r\n- [ ] Address suffix should reflect network preferences (`eth:` in blue if mainnet is in preferences, `opt:` in red if Optimism is in preferences, `arb:` in turquoise if Arbitrum is in preferences). Default preferences are Mainnet and Optimism.\r\n- [ ] For this issue, networks preferences should not be editable. That will be implemented in a separate issue.\r\n- [ ] When user presses \"Save address\" button in the bottom sheet, address should be saved for the selected account, bottom sheet is dismissed, and in-app notification should be shown as in Figma design 5.\r\n- [] status go rpc event should be fired and the data should be persisted\r\n-[] toast shows once the event has fired\r\n\r\nFeel free to break up this issue in smaller issues if necessary",
